  94:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** // DEBUG: added for the "app hangs after bootloader jump" investigation.
  95:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** // Handler was previously empty (just while(1)), so a real CPU fault (bad jump,
  96:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** // invalid memory access, etc.) would look identical to any other kind of silent
  97:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** // hang -- no way to tell them apart from the UART log alone.
  98:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** //
  99:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** // This C function does the actual logging. It must be called with the MSP value
 100:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** // exactly as it was at exception entry, read by the naked asm trampoline below
 101:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** // BEFORE any C function prologue gets a chance to touch the stack (reading MSP
 102:Core/Src/stm32h5xx_it.c **** // from inside a normal C function is not reliably safe for this reason).
